      I’m Bradley Matera. I build software with a focus on reliability, clarity, and maintainability. I care about interfaces that feel straightforward to use, backends that behave consistently, and documentation that makes projects understandable to the next developer who opens the repo.
      </p>
      <p>
        I've completed my B.S. in Web Development at Full Sail University. In 2025, I also completed an AWS Cloud Support Engineering internship, where I worked with real cloud infrastructure, internal support tooling, and incident workflows. That experience gave me direct exposure to how production systems behave, how failures surface, and how better tooling and documentation prevent repeat issues.
      </p>
      <p>
        Before moving into tech, I served as a U.S. Army combat medic and later worked in operations, construction, and case management roles. Those environments required staying calm under pressure, communicating clearly, and following structured processes. I apply the same habits in software work: observe the issue, trace the root cause, fix it cleanly, and document the outcome.
      </p>
      <p>
        Today I build full-stack web applications, local AI experiments, and cloud-hosted services. I'm especially interested in infrastructure, DevOps workflows, and applied AI systems, and I spend time improving how projects are structured so they are easier to deploy, debug, and hand off.
      </p>
      <p>
        I'm looking for a team where I can contribute dependable systems, continue growing as an engineer, and ship real products that stay stable after release.
      </p>
